class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {
        int i=0;
        int j=nums.length-1;
        while(i<=j){
            int mid=(i+j)/2;
            if(nums[mid]==target) return mid;
            if(target<nums[mid]){
                j=mid-1;
            }
            else{
            i=mid+1;
            }
        }
        return i;
    }
}
Note: This approach uses binary search on the sorted array to efficiently find the target or its correct insert position.
We repeatedly calculate the middle index and compare the target with nums[mid]; if the target is smaller we search the left 
half (j = mid - 1), otherwise we search the right half (i = mid + 1). If the loop ends without finding the target, the pointer i 
indicates the position where the target should be inserted to maintain the sorted order.
